    },
    "launch-day-production-switch": {
      "id": "launch-day-production-switch",
      "name": "LAUNCH DAY — Production Switch (last-minute credential flip)",
      "content": "<p><strong>LAUNCH DAY — the last-minute production switch.</strong> Everything in this node is deliberately deferred until we go fully public. Throughout the beta we stay on Clerk's <em>free development keys</em> so nothing starts costing money and beta invites keep working. Do ALL of these together in ONE dedicated session on the day we go public — doing them piecemeal forces repeated user re-invites and multi-system updates.</p><p><strong>Clerk — development → production (where paid usage begins):</strong></p><ul data-type=\"taskList\"><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Flip the IdiamPro app from Development to Production in the Clerk dashboard (one-way switch)</p></div></li><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Verify the 2ndbrainware.com domain with Clerk and generate the new production keys</p></div></li><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Update the two Clerk keys in Vercel, add the sign-up webhook, remove the \"Development mode\" banner</p></div></li><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Re-invite Kathy and every beta user — development accounts do NOT carry over to production</p></div></li></ul><p><strong>Storage (Upstash) — rotate and re-wire:</strong></p><ul data-type=\"taskList\"><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Replace the manually-added storage credentials in Vercel with the auto-syncing integration, then rotate the token</p></div></li><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Write-probe: submit a test application and confirm it lands in the admin Pending list</p></div></li></ul><p><strong>Cleanup &amp; final sanity:</strong></p><ul data-type=\"taskList\"><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Revoke the temporary Vercel access tokens created during June setup</p></div></li><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Sign in as howard, confirm the admin dashboard opens; have Kathy re-onboard from a fresh invite</p></div></li><li data-type=\"taskItem\" data-checked=\"false\"><label><input type=\"checkbox\"></label><div><p>Confirm the \"Development mode\" banner is gone; bump the Launch Progress outline to the production-credentials milestone</p></div></li></ul><p><em>Tracked in Claude Code as the \"LAUNCH DAY\" task. Full technical detail lives in the production-migration-checklist memory.</em></p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "roadmap-m6-launch",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2.6.1"
    }
  },
